From a4b96e2407beec72cbd73db35c32730eaacb21f2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sarika Sharma <sarishar@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 18 Aug 2025 20:56:41 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:DP: wifi:cfg80211: Increase buffer size for
 get_station command

Currently, the buffer size allocated for the get_station command in
nl80211_get_station is NLMSG_DEFAULT_SIZE, which is insufficient
to send the output to user-space and returns buffer full error.

Hence to fix, increase the buffer size to 4096 bytes. This ensures
the get_station command can return complete station information.

Fixes: I316b5ff8418 ("UPSTREAM:DP: wifi:cfg80211/mac80211: add support to handle per link statistics of multi-link station")
Signed-off-by: Sarika Sharma <sarishar@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 net/wireless/nl80211.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/net/wireless/nl80211.c b/net/wireless/nl80211.c
index eb3b6e8..3694b08 100644
--- a/net/wireless/nl80211.c
+++ b/net/wireless/nl80211.c
@@ -8540,7 +8540,7 @@ static int nl80211_get_station(struct sk_buff *skb, struct genl_info *info)
 		return err;
 	}
 
-	msg = nlmsg_new(NLMSG_DEFAULT_SIZE, GFP_KERNEL);
+	msg = nlmsg_new(4096, GFP_KERNEL);
 	if (!msg) {
 		cfg80211_sinfo_release_content(&sinfo);
 		return -ENOMEM;
-- 
2.34.1

